 We have re-evaluated (n,xn) reactions on Ir-191 in view of recent7725 1451
GEANIE data on gamma-rays observed in the entire decay chain of   7725 1451
isotopes following the n+Ir-191 reaction. Those data led to a     7725 1451
much clearer understanding of the low-lying levels structure of   7725 1451
the iridium isotopes. In addition GEANIE data provided a powerful 7725 1451
probe to the spin distributions in the excited nuclei following   7725 1451
the initial reaction.                                             7725 1451
                                                                  7725 1451
New GNASH model calculations were performed, using the newer      7725 1451
levels schemes observed by Fotiades et al. at LANSCE [Fo05], and  7725 1451
earlier on by Garrett et al. [Ga96,Ga00].                         7725 1451
                                                                  7725 1451
The quantum-mechanical FKK approach to pre-equilibrium was used   7725 1451
to compute the residual spin distribution following the           7725 1451
precompound stage. Compared to the default compound nucleus spin  7725 1451
distribution, The FKK spin distribution is shifted toward lower   7725 1451
values and has a strong impact on the prediction of gamma-lines   7725 1451
excitation function. This is particularly true for gamma-rays     7725 1451
observed between high-spin states, which are depopulated by the   7725 1451
pre-equilibrium phase [Ka05].                                     7725 1451
                                                                  7725 1451
Modifications of the earlier evaluation are summarized below:     7725 1451
                                                                  7725 1451
 - an additional isomeric state in Ir-190 has been included at    7725 1451
   36.1 keV, (4)+, and T_1/2 = 1.4 ms [Ne06].                     7725 1451
                                                                  7725 1451
 - the (n,2n) isomer production cross sections have been split    7725 1451
   into four sections corresponding to the following final        7725 1451
   states in Ir-190:                                              7725 1451
                                                                  7725 1451
        - ground-state, 0., 4-, 11.78 d                           7725 1451
        - m1, 26.1 keV, (1-), 1.12 h                              7725 1451
        - m2, 36.1 keV, (4)+, 1.4 ms                              7725 1451
        - m3, 376.4 keV, (11)-, 3.087 h                           7725 1451
                                                                  7725 1451
 - the total (n,2n) cross section has been adjusted below 10      7725 1451
   MeV to better agree with the Bayhurst data point at 9.34 MeV.  7725 1451
   This adjustment was performed on the g, m1 and m2 states.      7725 1451
                                                                  7725 1451
 - the (n,3n) cross section correspond to the new GNASH result.   7725 1451
                                                                  7725 1451
In order to compare with the (n,2n) cross section activation data 7725 1451
by Bayhurst, the evaluated (n,2n) g+m1+m2+8.6%m3 should be used.  7725 1451
The 8.6% value corresponds to the part of the m3-isomer that      7725 1451
decays through g-ray, while 91.4% disappears by electron capture. 7725 1451
The 8.6% is the value obtained by Garrett et al. [Ga00], and is   7725 1451
only slightly different from the 5.6% used in previous works.     7725 1451
